## Context
Top level reached 43 entries with two flat mega-directories: `scripts/` (173
files mixing library, entry points, plotting) and `content/` (~7 deliverables
sharing one Quarto project, forcing exclusion-mask profile files). Target state,
placement rule, and the 19-file migration audit are in `docs/repo-layout.md`.

This is a **tracking ticket** for the CODE + PROSE axis of the repo reorg. Work
proceeds in stages ("ranger la chambre en plusieurs temps"): code, prose. It
stays open until its children close.

## Relationship to 0221 (read first)
`0221` is the pre-existing reorg tracker; it owns the **data-layout** axis
(`data/catalogs` = Phase 1 / `data/derived` = Phase 2), with children `0218`
and `0222`, and it codified the governing principle in the canonical rules doc
`.claude/rules/architecture.md` (§ Project structure, § Data location, §
Artifact homes by phase). This ticket does **not** duplicate that; the former
DATA workstream `0224` was closed as a duplicate of `0221`/`0218`/`0222`.
`0223` extends the same reorg onto code and prose, and must stay consistent
with `architecture.md` and 0221's "flat by phase, NOT by workpackage" rule.

## Author ratification (2026-07-10) — resolved
- **`deliverables/` per-paper Quarto — RATIFIED.** Proceed with the prose
  reorg (0226); `architecture.md` § Project structure to be updated to match
  when the move lands.
- **`src/climatefinance/` — DECLINED.** Keep the existing library convention
  (`_`-private + `pipeline_*` loaders in `scripts/`; `libs/` for cross-repo
  sharing). Code reorg (0225) is now phase sub-grouping + in-place extractions,
  no `src/`, no `python -m` flip.
- **Shared harvest + indexing for AEDIST → `libs/`, not `src/`.** The author
  foresees corpus harvesting + indexing shared with AEDIST. That is cross-repo,
  so it grows `libs/openalex-corpus` (harvest, exists) + indexing (to add),
  consumed by AEDIST via git source. Tracked as seed `0229`.

## Children
- `0225` — Workstream CODE (src/ + scripts/ reorg)
- `0226` — Workstream PROSE (deliverables/ Quarto reorg)

## Scheduling — after the Œconomia resubmit
The resubmit is the deadline track; the reorg is tidying with no deadline
payoff. CODE (`0225`) rewrites import paths + Make invocations, PROSE (`0226`)
moves `manuscript.qmd` into `deliverables/manuscript/` — both destabilize the
exact machinery the resubmission build depends on. Sequence both **after** the
resubmit ships. DATA (`0224`, en cours) is Quarto/import-independent and may
continue in parallel, but only if its moves do not touch DVC stages the
resubmit build reads; otherwise freeze it too.

## Relevant files
- `docs/repo-layout.md` — target tree, placement rule, layering invariant, ordered moves

## Exit criteria
- All three workstream children closed
- Integration review: `make clean && make all` green from the reorganized tree
- Root entry count materially reduced; no flat 170-file directory remains
